title: 820-00239-09  No boot
message:
Hi all!

Customer report that the machine works perfect yesterday evening, but this morning macbook won't turn on.
CPU Vcore steady at 1.07v measured on L7210/L7220 so no boot I guess.

with another bin came from this forum (filename "A1706 820-00239-09 - clean.bin") , Vcore stays at 0v.
Where should I start?
Thank you

title: 820-00239-09  No boot
message:
Then probably bad CPU.

PLT_RESET_L comes high?

title: 820-00239-09  No boot
message: PLT_RST_L comes high after a few seconds and stay high at 3.33v stable

title: 820-00239-09  No boot
message: So nothing that I can do? :(

title: 820-00239-09  No boot
message:
If PLT_RST_L comes high power on sequence is completed and remains a problem related with data communication between the chips.
Just in case, check all resistors from LPC bus, R1320-7.
Also check all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and their traces.
You can try to heat CPU with quality flux; in case of accumulated crap underneath.
